article.headline: Michigan State coach McCallie earns 300th career win
article.linkText: Michigan State coach McCallie earns 300th career win
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Allyssa DeHaan scored 17 points, Victoria Lucas-Perry had 15, and Aisha Jefferson added 12 to lead Michigan State to a 69-45 victory over UC Santa Barbara on Wednesday night.

Lucas-Perry scored all her points in the second half for the No. 20 Spartans (8-2), after UCSB took a 27-26 halftime lead on Jordan Franey's two 3-pointers.

Jenna Green led the Gauchos (4-7) with 13 points and nine rebounds. Franey scored 12.

Spartans coach Joanne P. McCallie earned her 300th career victory. She is in her seventh season at Michigan State after eight years at Maine.
